---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseHead />
<Header />

<!-- Retro News Ticker -->
<div style="background-color: #000080; color: white; padding: 5px 0; font-size: 14px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden;">
  <marquee behavior="scroll" direction="left" scrollamount="4">
    📢 [1999∞] EctoCorp assures all associates that productivity remains at optimal levels — 
    🚨 Reminder: Unauthorized messaging is a Class-2 Violation — 
    📞 Report suspicious communications to 9966 immediately — 
    📰 New morale posters available in all approved break areas — 
    ⏰ All clocks inspected and functioning as scheduled —
  </marquee>
</div>

<main class="container">
  <h2>Broadcast & Messaging Bureau</h2>

  <div style="background-color: #fff8c6; border: 1px solid #999; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 14px;">
    ⚠️ Access to restricted messaging channels without clearance is a violation of Section 4-C of the Public Communications Guide.
  </div>

  <form style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <label for="message-search"><b>Search Public Bulletin Archive:</b></label><br />
    <input type="text" id="message-search" name="message-search" placeholder="Enter keyword..." size="30" disabled style="margin-top: 5px;">
    <p style="font-size: 10px; color: gray;">* Archive search is temporarily offline for content alignment review.</p>
  </form>

  <p>
    The Broadcast & Messaging Bureau ensures all communications — from company news to public service announcements — meet EctoCorp’s standards for morale, compliance, and accuracy.
    Every poster, newswire, and public statement passes through our desks before reaching Associates.
  </p>

  <p><b>Department Head:</b> Director of Broadcast & Messaging</p>

  <p><b>Key Responsibilities:</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Review and approve all public communications</li>
    <li>Manage the Authorized Morale Library (AML)</li>
    <li>Oversee Emergency Broadcast Procedures</li>
    <li>Monitor for unauthorized or non-compliant messaging</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 12px; color: gray;">
    Last reviewed: 1999.4.2 · All messaging is monitored for quality and tone.
  </p>

  <hr />
  <p><b>Navigate to Other Departments:</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/departments/hr">Human Resources</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/legal">The Legal Department</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/temporal">Department of Temporal Investigations</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/nutrition">Consumer Nutritional Division</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/housing">Infrastructure & Housing Authority</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/external">Department of External Affairs</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/productivity">Human Productivity Division</a></li>
    <li><a href="/departments/ced">Compliance Enforcement Division</a></li>
  </ul>
</main>

<Footer />
